owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: references the person or device that performed the activity,usually used in provvenance

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A property that points to the display algorithm for this particular entity

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Points to the field in the implmented database scheme which is used as the subtype indicator during query or fiing of data

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: points to the category of attendance whether first, subsequent, planned or unplanned

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is a record of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: points to the record or encounter section heading that this component is part of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is under heading of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Points to the method of admission such as whether from waiting list, booked or from A&e or direct from GP

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Points to the source of admission of the patient
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has admission source

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Treatment function / speciality service for which admitted

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: treatment function type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An agent acting on behalf of another agent or organisation. tHE the assignment of authority and responsibility to an agent (by itself or by another agent) to carry out a specific activity as a delegate or representative, while the agent it acts on behalf of retains some responsibility for the outcome of the delegated work.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: acted on behalf of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship between one entity and another (node to node in graph terms) where the entities are instantiated as complex objects in the data store. For example, a reference to a colour or disease would be a data model object property, but the relationship between a patient and health event would be a relationship sub property
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: data model relationship

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A dependent relationship is where the source entity depends on the presence of the target entity to exist i.e. is a component of it or some business process requires it. An example of this is that a hospital admission encounter is dependent on an inpatient stay encounter
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dependent relationship

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Entity may contain subcomponents
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has component

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: references the organisation that is the data controller of the record entry (or sub organisation of that data controller)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has data controller

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: points to the patient this record is about
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has subject

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: the entity is part of another entity e.g. a parent observation
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is component of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: References the entry that the organisation is data controller of. Inverse property of 'has data controller'
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is data controller for

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: references the entries that this object is the subject of e.g. Patient 'is subject of' Encounter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A section is a subsection of another section
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is subsection of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: points to the encounter this is part of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: sub property of health event responsible agent, pointing to a practitioner

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: High level property indicating the person responsible for the event,if the event is a recording of something seen, done, thought or measured. This is an abstract property which is specialised in the data model for the particular health entries. Implementation schema maps can map at this level in order to have one field throughout the data base (e.g. agent or user) to mean the same thing
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: responsible agent

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A provenance property indicating that something was used. it is the beginning of utilizing an entity by an activity.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: usually used in provenance to associate an activity or entity with an agent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: was associated with

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The ascribing of an entity to an agent.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: was attributed to

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: references a resource from which the resource or entry was transformed from
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: was derived from

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An entity was generated by a provenance activity

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: points to a time period type such as night time or day time
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has time aspect

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: a device used by a procedure or observation or encounter

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: date and time of the update

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A data property that has a date and time as a value
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: date time property

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: order of display for this entity in relation to sibling entities
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: display order

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: the date and time of the creation or update to the component
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has component date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A date and time a particular entry or component was made (local time)
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has Date and time of entry

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The effective start date and time relevant to the event being described (and not related to the entry date into the system)
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start date/time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: the effective end date/time relevant to the event being described

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has identifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: First Accident and Emergency Attendance - the first in a series, or the only attendance, in a particular Accident and Emergency Episode CDS 1
owl:Class.rdfs:label: First Accident and Emergency Attendance in episode

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Follow-up Accident and Emergency Attendance - planned: a subsequent planned attendance at the same department, and for the same incident as the first attendance CDS 2
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subsequent planned A&E attendance at same department, and incident

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Follow-up Accident and Emergency Attendance - unplanned: a subsequent unplanned attendance at the same department, and for the same incident as the first attendance CDS 3
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subsequent unplanned A&E attendance at the same department and incident

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An indication of whether an APPOINTMENT for a CARE CONTACT took place.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Attended or not attended

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether the A&E attendance is first or a follow up
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Accident and emergency attendance or follow up

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency departments are a CONSULTANT led 24 hour service with full resuscitation facilities and designated accommodation for the reception of accident and emergency PATIENTS CDS type 1
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Consultant led A&E department with full facilities (department type)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Consultant led mono specialty accident and emergency service (e.g. ophthalmology, dental) with designated accommodation for the reception of PATIENTS CDS 2
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mono speciality A&E (department type)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Other type of A&E/minor injury ACTIVITY with designated accommodation for the reception of accident and emergency PATIENTS. The department may be doctor led or NURSE led and treats at least minor injuries and illnesses and can be routinely accessed without APPOINTMENT. A SERVICE mainly or entirely APPOINTMENT based (for example a GP Practice or Out-Patient Clinic) is excluded even though it may treat a number of PATIENTS with minor illness or injury. Excludes NHS walk-in centres CDS 3
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Minor injuries unit either Doctor or Nurse led (department type)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: NHS walk in centres CDS 4
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NHS Walk in centre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: End of the A&E attendance including transfer
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Accident and emergency encounter discharge

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An A&E department or equivalent setting
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Accident and emergency (setting)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A status that is in active or active
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Activity status

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The active-inactive status value is active
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Active status

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Admission method relating to the admission of the baby i.e. the baby is the subject of the admission
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Baby related admission (admission method)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A PATIENT admitted electively during the course of a day with the intention of receiving care who does not require the use of a Hospital Bed overnight and who returns home as scheduled. If this original intention is not fulfilled and the PATIENT stays overnight, such a PATIENT should be counted as an ordinary admission CDS type 2
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Day case admission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Mother and baby using Delivery facilities only and not using a Hospital Bed in the Antenatal or Postnatal WARDS during the stay in hospital
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mother and baby using delivery facilities only

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A PATIENT not admitted electively, and any PATIENT admitted electively with the expectation that they will remain in hospital for at least one night, including a PATIENT admitted with this intention who leaves hospital for any reason without staying overnight. A PATIENT admitted electively with the intent of not staying overnight, but who does not return home as scheduled, should be counted as an ordinary admission CDS 1
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ordinary non elective admission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A PATIENT admitted electively during the day, as part of a planned series of regular admissions for an on-going regime of broadly similar treatment and who is discharged the same day. If the intention is not fulfilled and one of these admissions should involve a stay of at least 24 hours, such an admission should be classified as an ordinary admission. The series of regular admissions ends when the PATIENT no longer requires frequent admissions
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Regular elective day admission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A PATIENT admitted electively for the night, as part of a planned series of regular admissions for an on-going regime of broadly similar treatment and who is discharged in the morning. If the intention is not fulfilled and one of these admissions should involve a stay of at least 24 hours, such an admission should be classified as an ordinary admission. The series of regular admissions ends when the patient no longer requires frequent admissions
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Regular elective night admission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency admssion after Baby born at home as intended CDS type 2C
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission after baby born at home as intended

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: after a request for immediate admission has been made direct to a Hospital Provider from a bed bureau - CDS type 23
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission via bed bureau

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Birth of a baby in this Health Care Provider CDS type 82
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Birth of a baby in this Health Care Provider

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Baby born outside the Health Care Provider except when born at home as intended type 83
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Baby born outside the Health Care Provider except when born at home as intended

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elective booked admission CDS type 12
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Booked admission (admssion method)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency admission from Accident and Emergency Department of another provider where the PATIENT had not been admitted CDS type 2A
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission from A&E from another provider

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency admission from Consultant Clinic, of this or another Health Care Provider - CDS type 24
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission from consultant clinic

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergencey admission - Other emergency admission CDS type 2D replacing CDS type 28 also
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission via other or none specific means

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The method of admission is elective
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Elective admission method

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency Admission, when admission is unpredictable and at short notice because of clinical need
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission (admission method)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency admission via GENERAL PRACTITIONER: after a request for immediate admission has been made direct to a Hospital Provider, i.e. not through a Bed bureau, by a GENERAL PRACTITIONER or deputy - CDS type 22
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission direct from GP

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Emergency admission - Transfer of an admitted PATIENT from another Hospital Provider in an emergency - CDS type 2B
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission - transfer of admitted patient from another hospital

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Maternit admission antepartum CDS type 31
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Maternity admission ante partum

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Maternity admission post partum CDS type 32
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Maternity admission post partum

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Maternity Admission, of a pregnant or recently pregnant woman to a maternity WARD (including Delivery facilities) except when the intention is to terminate the pregnancy
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Maternity Admission, of a pregnant or recently pregnant woman

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Admission via Mental Health Crisis Resolution Team CDS type 25
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Emergency admission via mental health crisis resolution team

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Planned admission - CDS type 13
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Planned admission (admission method)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Method of actual admission was electively from the waiting list CDS type 11
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Waiting list (admission method)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Transfer of any admitted PATIENT from other Hospital Provider other than in an emergency cds TYPE 81
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Non emergency transfer from other provider

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: NHS PATIENT, including Overseas Visitors charged under the National Health Service (Overseas Visitors Hospital Charging Regulations) CDS 01
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NHS PATIENT/ Overseas Visitor charged under NHS

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Private PATIENT, one who uses accommodation or SERVICES authorised under the National Health Service Act 2006 cds 02
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Private PATIENTusing accommodation/service authorised under the NHS

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Amenity PATIENT, one who pays for the use of a single room or small ward in accordance with the National Health Service Act 2006 cds 03
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Amenity PATIENT,use of NHS single room / small ward

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Category II PATIENT, one for whom work is undertaken by hospital medical or dental staff within category II as defined in paragraph 37 of the Terms and Conditions of Service of Hospital Medical and Dental Staff 04
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Category II PATIENT

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
This is recorded for PATIENT ACTIVITY.
A PATIENT who is an Overseas Visitor does not qualify for free NHS healthcare and can choose to pay for NHS treatment or for private treatment. If they pay for NHS treatment then they should be recorded as NHS PATIENTS.
The PATIENT's ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY CODE may change during an episode or spell. For example, the PATIENT may opt to change from NHS to private health care. In this case, the start and end dates for each new ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY PERIOD (episode or spell) should be recorded.
If the ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY CODE changes during a Hospital Provider Spell the ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY CODE (ON ADMISSION) is used to derive the 'Category of PATIENT' for Hospital Episode Statistics (HES).
The category 'amenity PATIENT' is only applicable to PATIENTS using a Hospital Bed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Administrative category code (NHS DD)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of encounter involving any admin entry into the records such as a filing of a report or note about the patient that defines the type of encounter entered into the health record

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: criticl care period for an adult
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Adult critical care encounter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Not applicable - APPOINTMENT occurs in the future CDS 0
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Not applicable - appointment occurs in the future

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: APPOINTMENT cancelled by, or on behalf of, the PATIENT CDS 2
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cancelled by, or on behalf of, the patient

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Attended on time or, if late, before the relevant CARE PROFESSIONAL was ready to see the PATIENT CDS 5

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Arrived late, after the relevant CARE PROFESSIONAL was ready to see the PATIENT, but was seen CDS 6
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Arrived late, after the professional was ready to see the patient, but was seen

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Discharged from care - last attendance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Another APPOINTMENT given CDS 2
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Another appointment given

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A setting in which care takes place (e.g. in an encounter)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Care setting

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Non standard LOCATION using the operating department
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Critical care non standard location

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Adult (PATIENTS more than 19 years old on admission predominate)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Critical care unit adult facilities

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Non-specific, general adult critical care PATIENTS predominate CDS01
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Critical care general adult facility

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Renal adult PATIENTS predominate CDS 10

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data model

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A record entry about an encounter, which is an interaction between a patient (or on behalf of the patient) and a health professional or health provider. It includes consultations as well as care processes such as admission, discharges. It also includes the noting of a filing of a document or report. Each encounter subclass is given a type which is then used to determine the additional properties expected in the record. Specialised encounters are further defined as subclasses by additional properties commensurate with the encounter type
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Encounter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A query or formula based derived value for use in the data model. Typical example might be an age or ethnicity. The definition uses Information model extended query language and therefore contains elements that are not supported by OWL
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Functional value concept

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A major provenanced entry in a health record. Something relating to health that has happened over a period of time, or is planned to happen at a time in the future. The main differentiator between this and other events is that the state relating to the event lasts as long as the event. States that last longer, such as paient demographics, regisatrion, or problems are modelled in related entities
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Health event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entry recording the event of a hospital admission. Has specialised properties
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hospital admission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entry describing the event of a hospital discharge. Has specialised encounter properties
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hospital discharge (entry)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entry describing the stay of a patient in hospital. As well as spcialised properties it has sub component encounters of admission and discharge
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hospital inpatient stay

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entry describing a hospital outpatient attendance
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hospital outpatient encounter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entity or individual that can be identified in a unique way. May be a living being such as a person, or an instutition, device, or location
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifiable entity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An identifier for an identifiable entity consisting of a code and scheme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actual location for some activity. It is associated with geospacial coordinates and properties and addresses
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Location

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A patient health event which is an observation relating to the state of a patient including things observed, done, and measured or noted. Observations have specialised sub types

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The activity that took place at this point in the provenance of an entry. This normally instantiated as a subtype e.g. filing of a record. An implementation map is likely to have a type field pointing to the subtype applying the "entity subtype" map method.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Provenance activity (entry)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A record of the provenance of an entry in a data store
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Provenance entity (entry)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Is a subheading within an encounter record
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Encounter section header

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Information about a person related to the patient in some way. If the related person is not in the record store, the entity may contain information about the person. If the related person is known to be in the record store, and identified may point to that person entry.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Related person

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entry describing the state of something such as a person demographic entry , an organisation directory, or more abstract things like a problem. They are usually related to an identifiable entity. For example a person demographic is related to a person and an organisation details entry is related to an organisation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: State entry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A specialised structure forming part of a record or directory entry. These sructures canno stand alone i.e. must be part of, or referred to, by a record entry or directory entry
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Structural artefact

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Maternity admission record derived from either admission method or admission classification of patient
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Maternity admission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A concept that is defined by a combination of ontology and data model attributes
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Query concept

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A person in the role of a patient
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Patient

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An individual human being
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Person

owl:Class.rdfs:label: At night
